Description: The role of chat message: user - User entering chat message, assistant - GenAI's response to user's message, system - system generated message, tool - A tool like code interpreter (Python), web browser, file handler, or image generator was invoked by the assistant to perform a task
The name of the tool used

Example: How to control kodi via Amazon alexa
Description: The message content entered by user or generated by assistant / system
Format or nature of the message content, helping ChatGPT's interface determine how to render that message. It's especially useful when the message isn't just plain text
Specifies input or output modalities beyond text (only set when content_type is set to multimodal_text)
Default model set in user settings
Indicates if chat_message was created during a voice interaction
List of sources that the assistant included to back up its responses

Example: [{"domain": "walmart.com", "entries": [{"type": "search_result", "title": "17 Travel Backpack Carry-on Laptop Backpack Overnight Bag Weekender", "url": "https://www.walmart.com/ip/17-Travel-Backpack-Carry-on-Laptop-Backpack-Overnight-Bag-Weekender-Bag-Casual-Daypack-for-Women-Men-College-Pink/5388256876"}]}]
Description: Search results that were retrieved during a conversation
Indicates is user is on free or paid subscription
